    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 28 article about decline in sales at Levi Strauss &amp; Co, which misstated Pepsi-Cola's soft-drink market share (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article last Sunday about sales declines at Levi Strauss &amp; Company misstated the domestic market share achieved by Pepsi-Cola in 1998 and 1999, when Pepsi's North American division was headed by Philip A. Marineau, now Levi's chief executive. Pepsi's market share, for colas and all soft drinks, was essentially flat; it did not surpass Coca-Cola's.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
